From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: OpenEuler Embedded <openeuler-embedded@openeuler.org>
Date: Thu, 01 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] load_policy: guard malloc_trim() with __GLIBC__

malloc_trim() is a glibc extension that is not available in musl libc.
The call is only a hint to the allocator to release unused memory back
to the OS; it has no effect on correctness. Guard it so the code
compiles cleanly against musl.

Upstream-Status: Pending
Signed-off-by: OpenEuler Embedded <openeuler-embedded@openeuler.org>
---
 src/load_policy.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/load_policy.c b/src/load_policy.c
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/src/load_policy.c
+++ b/src/load_policy.c
@@ -367,7 +367,9 @@ int selinux_init_load_policy(int *enforce)
 
 	/* Load the policy. */
 	rc = selinux_mkload_policy(0);
+#ifdef __GLIBC__
 	malloc_trim(0);
+#endif
 	return rc;
 
       noload:
